			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Melee getting weak.....<a name="5984"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 4 03 7:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My favorite weapons skill building spot for 35 to 40 are the crazed goblins in Butcherblock Mountains.  The nice thing about this camp is that there are three goblins that spawn about every five minutes and they're spaced far enough apart that they will not aggro when pulled in order of spawn.
<br />

<br />
My typical song lineup for these guys is...
<br />

<br />
1. Selo's Consonant Chains
<br />
2. Jonothan's Whisteling War Song
<br />
3. Anthem De Arms
<br />
4. Psalm of Warmth
<br />
5. Amplification
<br />
6. Charm of some sort
<br />

<br />
Chains is probably the most important song to get to stick and I typically pull with it as I can have my twist running and be back on Chains by the time the gobby gets to my pull spot.
<br />
I'm not totally sure if the haste of Jonothan's and Anthem stack, but frankly I can do more damage with these two songs than any other combo I've tried, remember this is level 35-40 not 50+.
<br />
Charm is nice to have up so that if you have a bit of trouble you can just charm the bugger and take care of your problem by running to the PoK book or just getting some health back and reapplying charm as needed.
<br />

<br />
Another delight to this camp is that the gobbies drop up to 4pp each and very commonly drop ringmail armor and fine steel daggers which sell for 4 to 5pp each.  As well the xp for levels 35-40 isn't all that bad so you aren't completely wasting time here.
<br />

<br />
You will also find that these gobbies are tough enough that they last a while which is important because you are not going to build your skill too quickly if the mob is dead in a couple of whacks.
<br />

<br />
Another thing about this camp is that you will get bugged by Paladins because this is where the Blade of Nobility drops.  As well I typically shout out that the blade dropped so hopefully someone will come get it.  Sadly I have seen this thing rot more times than I can remember only to have a Paladin send me a tell some time after asking if I could send him a tell if it drops.
<br />

<br />
Merry Journies all may our songs be heard as one</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=641487">Muse Ellorra Dannen</a><br>
Bard of the 65th Song<br><br>

Myrrialle Thuleanna<br>
Druid of the 55th Ring<br>

Innoruuk Server</span></td>
